The White House has issued Executive Order 13553, which designates Iranian officials responsible for or complicit in serious human rights abuses. The order blocks the property and interests in property of these individuals, preventing them from being transferred, paid, exported, withdrawn, or otherwise dealt with. The order applies to officials of the Government of Iran or persons acting on behalf of the government who have committed serious human rights abuses against individuals in Iran or Iranian citizens or residents since June 12, 2009. It also includes individuals who have provided support or assistance to these activities. The order prohibits donations to these individuals and their affiliates and imposes sanctions on any person or entity that attempts to evade or violate the order. The Secretary of the Treasury and the Secretary of State are authorized to take necessary actions to enforce the order. The order is effective as of September 29, 2010.